- 1 -

(4) Provide information on system and outcome areas needing
improvement and identifying barriers to system delivery; and
(5) Engage existing regional or county level advisory entities, such as the
local advisory boards established under § 37-5-607 or citizen review panels
required by 42 U.S.C. § 5106a to provide feedback, when appropriate, on
departmental practices.
(d) The statewide quality assurance program may also create and engage new
regional or county level advisory entities in addition to those under subdivision (c)(5) in
order to provide feedback, when appropriate, on departmental practices.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it.
